(4)

The other loss function (5) is based on the popular Bayesian Personalized Ranking (BPR) Rendle et al. (2009a) loss. Here the negative log-probability of the target score exceeding the sample scores is minimized (i.e. the probability of target scores being above sample scores is maximized). The non-continuous P (ri > rj) is approximated by (ri - rj).

